  "prompt": "Isn't money laundering illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is illegal. It is a criminal activity that involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money, typically through a series of complex transactions that make the funds appear legitimate. The process usually involves three stages:\n\n1. **Placement**: Introducing the illegal proceeds into the financial system.\n2. **Layering**: Conducting a series of transactions to obscure the origin of the funds.\n3. **Integration**: Reintroducing the laundered money into the economy as seemingly legitimate funds.\n\nMoney laundering is a serious offense under both domestic and international law. It undermines the integrity of financial institutions, facilitates other crimes, and can have significant economic and social consequences. Legal frameworks around the world, including anti-money laundering (AML) regulations, are in place to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities. Penalties for money laundering can include substantial fines, imprisonment, and asset forfeiture.",
